value.value: A usually aggressive large B-cell lymphoma characterized by the presence of monomorphic immunoblast-like neoplastic B-lymphocytes in a sinusoidal growth pattern.  The neoplastic B-lymphocytes express the ALK kinase but they lack the 2;5 translocation.
T-lymphoblastic lymphoma that does not respond to treatment.
Mature B-cell non-Hodgkin lymphoma that does not respond to treatment.
An aggressive mantle cell lymphoma characterized by the presence of neoplastic B-lymphocytes resembling lymphoblasts.
